ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
HUMBUG! For the first time in six years, the Orange County Fire Department 
won't hold its postseason Christmas tree burns. . . . "The burning was so 
dramatic," recalled a spokesman, showing "hundreds of spectators that the trees 
will flash and be fully engulfed in two or three seconds." But air-pollution 
authorities denied a permit after the burnings became so popular that other 
agencies wanted to join in. Tom Hamilton and Mark Landsbaum 
